headline: US Owners See Value in English Football: Gary Neville
summary: Gary Neville, broadcaster, businessman and part owner of lower league football team Salford City, says American owners see real value in English clubs and will continue to buy in and invest in them. "Americans look at the price tags that are associated with clubs and actually it is very good value," Neville tells Bloomberg Television. The American insurance giant AIG has taken a minority stake in Salford.
